27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment removes the creation in the bill of the Transportation Project Selection
2299 Council and specifies that the statewide transportation project selection prioritization
3300 process is developed and managed by the Department of Transportation and the Maine
3311 Turnpike Authority, rather than the Transportation Project Selection Council. The
3322 amendment also requires, in developing the prioritization process, the department and the
3333 Maine Turnpike Authority to weigh key goals under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 23,
3344 section 4209-B, subsection 1, paragraph D for each of the State's federally designated
3355 planning organization regions; solicit input from municipalities, counties and other
3366 planning organizations, transit operators, environmental groups, active transportation
3377 groups, economic development groups and other stakeholders in the development of the
3388 prioritization process; and make public, in an accessible format updated at least annually,
3399 a report with the results of the application of the prioritization process to projects, including
4400 how the weights of key goals were applied.
